<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Chaeyeon Kim — Creative Fellowship</title>
<style>
  @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=VT323&family=Space+Mono:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&display=swap');

  :root {
    --desktop-bg: #6b7c8f;
    --window-bg: #ececec;
    --window-border: #ffffff;
    --window-shadow: #00000055;
    --titlebar-active: linear-gradient(180deg, #6a9fd8 0%, #3a6ea5 100%);
    --titlebar-inactive: linear-gradient(180deg, #aaaaaa 0%, #888888 100%);
    --text-dark: #1a1a1a;
    --accent: #c0392b;
    --icon-label: #ffffff;
    --stress-low: #4a90d9;
    --stress-high: #c0392b;
  }

  * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }

  body {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    background: var(--desktop-bg);
    width: 100vw;
    height: 100vh;
    overflow: hidden;
    background-image:
      radial-gradient(ellipse at 20% 50%, #7a8fa3 0%, transparent 50%),
      radial-gradient(ellipse at 80% 20%, #5a6d80 0%, transparent 40%);
    cursor: default;
    user-select: none;
  }

  /* ── MENUBAR ── */
  #menubar {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0; left: 0; right: 0;
    height: 22px;
    background: rgba(30,30,30,0.85);
    backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0 12px;
    z-index: 9999;
    gap: 16px;
  }
  #menubar .apple { font-size: 14px; color: white; }
  #menubar span {
    font-size: 11px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85);
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }
  #menubar .right {
    margin-left: auto;
    display: flex;
    gap: 12px;
    align-items: center;
  }
  #clock {
    font-size: 11px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85);
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
  }

  /* ── DESKTOP ICONS ── */
  #desktop {
    position: fixed;
    top: 22px; left: 0; right: 0; bottom: 0;
    padding: 20px;
  }

  .icon-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 24px;
    position: absolute;
    right: 24px;
    top: 40px;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .icon {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 4px;
    cursor: pointer;
    width: 80px;
    transition: transform 0.1s;
  }

  .icon:hover { transform: scale(1.05); }
  .icon:active { transform: scale(0.96); }

  .icon-img {
    width: 52px;
    height: 52px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: 40px;
    filter: drop-shadow(0 2px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.4));
  }

  .icon-label {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--icon-label);
    text-align: center;
    text-shadow: 0 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,0.8), 0 0 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
    line-height: 1.3;
    max-width: 80px;
    word-break: break-word;
  }

  .icon.selected .icon-label {
    background: #0055cc;
    border-radius: 2px;
    padding: 1px 3px;
  }

  /* ── WINDOWS ── */
  .window {
    position: absolute;
    background: var(--window-bg);
    border: 1px solid #aaa;
    border-radius: 6px;
    box-shadow: 2px 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.4), inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.8);
    min-width: 320px;
    min-height: 200px;
    display: none;
    flex-direction: column;
    z-index: 100;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .window.active { z-index: 500; }
  .window.visible { display: flex; }

  .titlebar {
    background: var(--titlebar-active);
    height: 22px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0 8px;
    gap: 6px;
    cursor: move;
    border-radius: 6px 6px 0 0;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .window:not(.active) .titlebar {
    background: var(--titlebar-inactive);
  }

  .traffic-lights {
    display: flex;
    gap: 5px;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .tl {
    width: 12px; height: 12px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    cursor: pointer;
    border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .tl.close { background: #ff5f56; }
  .tl.min   { background: #ffbd2e; }
  .tl.max   { background: #27c93f; }
  .tl:hover { filter: brightness(1.1); }

  .titlebar-title {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.95);
    text-shadow: 0 1px 1px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
    margin: 0 auto;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
  }

  .window-content {
    padding: 16px;
    overflow-y: auto;
    flex: 1;
    font-size: 12px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--text-dark);
  }

  /* ── WINDOW: ABOUT ── */
  #win-about { top: 60px; left: 60px; width: 480px; height: 360px; }

  .about-header {
    display: flex;
    gap: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .about-avatar {
    width: 64px; height: 64px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #3a6ea5, #c0392b);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: 28px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    border: 2px solid #fff;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
  }

  .about-name {
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    color: #1a1a1a;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .about-subtitle {
    font-size: 10px;
    color: #666;
    margin-top: 4px;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .tag-row {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 6px;
    margin-top: 12px;
  }

  .tag {
    background: #1a1a1a;
    color: #fff;
    font-size: 9px;
    padding: 3px 8px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .tag.red { background: var(--accent); }
  .tag.blue { background: #3a6ea5; }

  /* ── WINDOW: CAPSTONE ── */
  #win-capstone { top: 80px; left: 200px; width: 520px; height: 420px; }

  .capstone-title {
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
    color: #1a1a1a;
  }

  .capstone-subtitle {
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--accent);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .section-label {
    font-size: 9px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: #999;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 14px 0 6px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
    padding-bottom: 4px;
  }

  .mechanism-box {
    background: #1a1a1a;
    color: #e8e8e8;
    padding: 12px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 10px 0;
  }

  .mechanism-box .highlight { color: #ff6b6b; }

  /* ── WINDOW: STRESS REACTIVE ── */
  #win-stress { top: 100px; left: 100px; width: 560px; height: 400px; }

  #stress-container {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    background: #0a0a0a;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 20px;
    transition: background 0.5s ease;
    border-radius: 0 0 4px 4px;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  #stress-container canvas {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0; left: 0;
    width: 100%; height: 100%;
  }

  #stress-ui {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 10;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 16px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  #stress-label {
    font-family: 'VT323', monospace;
    font-size: 48px;
    color: #fff;
    letter-spacing: 4px;
    text-shadow: 0 0 20px currentColor;
    transition: color 0.5s, text-shadow 0.5s;
  }

  #stress-bar-container {
    width: 300px;
    height: 12px;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.2);
  }

  #stress-bar {
    height: 100%;
    width: 20%;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, #4a90d9, #c0392b);
    border-radius: 6px;
    transition: width 0.3s ease;
  }

  #stress-desc {
    font-size: 10px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6);
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    max-width: 320px;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  #stress-btn {
    background: transparent;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.4);
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.8);
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    padding: 8px 20px;
    cursor: pointer;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    transition: all 0.2s;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  #stress-btn:hover {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
    border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.8);
    color: white;
  }

  #stress-mode-label {
    font-size: 9px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.4);
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  /* ── WINDOW: NOTEBOOK ── */
  #win-notebook { top: 120px; left: 140px; width: 500px; height: 380px; }

  .notebook-intro {
    background: #fff8e7;
    border-left: 3px solid #f0a500;
    padding: 10px 12px;
    font-size: 11px;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;
  }

  .audio-player {
    background: #1a1a1a;
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 14px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
  }

  .audio-title {
    font-size: 11px;
    color: #fff;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
  }

  .audio-subtitle {
    font-size: 9px;
    color: #888;
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
  }

  .audio-controls {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
  }

  .play-btn {
    width: 32px; height: 32px;
    background: var(--accent);
    border: none;
    border-radius: 50%;
    cursor: pointer;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: white;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    transition: transform 0.1s;
  }

  .play-btn:hover { transform: scale(1.1); }

  .audio-progress {
    flex: 1;
    height: 4px;
    background: #333;
    border-radius: 2px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .audio-progress-bar {
    width: 0%;
    height: 100%;
    background: var(--accent);
    border-radius: 2px;
    transition: width 0.1s;
  }

  .response-box {
    margin-top: 12px;
    background: #f0f0f0;
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 10px 12px;
    font-size: 11px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    border-left: 3px solid #3a6ea5;
    color: #333;
  }

  .response-box strong {
    display: block;
    font-size: 9px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: #3a6ea5;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }

  /* ── WINDOW: README ── */
  #win-readme { top: 90px; left: 80px; width: 440px; height: 340px; }

  .readme-content {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    line-height: 1.9;
    color: #333;
    white-space: pre-wrap;
  }

  .readme-content .comment { color: #999; }
  .readme-content .key { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 700; }
  .readme-content .value { color: #3a6ea5; }

  /* ── TRASH WINDOW ── */
  #win-trash { top: 110px; left: 120px; width: 420px; height: 300px; }

  .trash-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 10px;
    padding: 10px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #e0e0e0;
  }

  .trash-item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .trash-icon { font-size: 24px; flex-shrink: 0; }

  .trash-item-name {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #1a1a1a;
    margin-bottom: 3px;
  }

  .trash-item-desc {
    font-size: 10px;
    color: #666;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* ── DOCK ── */
  #dock {
    position: fixed;
    bottom: 8px;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.2);
    backdrop-filter: blur(20px);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 6px 12px;
    display: flex;
    gap: 8px;
    align-items: flex-end;
    z-index: 9998;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
  }

  .dock-item {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 3px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: transform 0.15s;
  }

  .dock-item:hover { transform: translateY(-8px) scale(1.2); }

  .dock-icon {
    width: 44px; height: 44px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: 26px;
    filter: drop-shadow(0 2px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.3));
  }

  .dock-label {
    font-size: 9px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9);
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    text-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.8);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .dock-dot {
    width: 4px; height: 4px;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  /* ── SCROLLBAR ── */
  ::-webkit-scrollbar { width: 8px; }
  ::-webkit-scrollbar-track { background: #e0e0e0; }
  ::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background: #aaa; border-radius: 4px; }

  /* ── ANIMATIONS ── */
  @keyframes windowOpen {
    from { transform: scale(0.92); opacity: 0; }
    to { transform: scale(1); opacity: 1; }
  }

  .window.visible { animation: windowOpen 0.15s ease-out; }

  @keyframes pulse {
    0%, 100% { opacity: 1; }
    50% { opacity: 0.4; }
  }

  .eeg-dot {
    display: inline-block;
    width: 6px; height: 6px;
    background: var(--accent);
    border-radius: 50%;
    animation: pulse 1.4s ease-in-out infinite;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- MENUBAR -->
<div id="menubar">
  <span class="apple">🧠</span>
  <span style="font-weight:700;">Chaeyeon Kim</span>
  <span>Google Creative Fellowship</span>
  <div class="right">
    <span>neuroscientist · composer · filmmaker · engineer</span>
    <span id="clock"></span>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- DESKTOP -->
<div id="desktop">

  <!-- DESKTOP ICONS -->
  <div class="icon-grid">

    <div class="icon" onclick="openWindow('win-about')">
      <div class="icon-img">👤</div>
      <div class="icon-label">README.txt</div>
    </div>

    <div class="icon" onclick="openWindow('win-capstone')">
      <div class="icon-img">📁</div>
      <div class="icon-label">The Body Conducts</div>
    </div>

    <div class="icon" onclick="openWindow('win-stress')">
      <div class="icon-img">🧠</div>
      <div class="icon-label">EEG_Simulator.app</div>
    </div>

    <div class="icon" onclick="openWindow('win-notebook')">
      <div class="icon-img">🎙️</div>
      <div class="icon-label">NotebookLM_Session</div>
    </div>

    <div class="icon" onclick="openWindow('win-trash')">
      <div class="icon-img">🗑️</div>
      <div class="icon-label">What AI Got Wrong</div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <!-- WINDOW: README -->
  <div class="window" id="win-about">
    <div class="titlebar" onmousedown="startDrag(event, 'win-about')">
      <div class="traffic-lights">
        <div class="tl close" onclick="closeWindow('win-about')"></div>
        <div class="tl min"></div>
        <div class="tl max"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="titlebar-title">README.txt</div>
    </div>
    <div class="window-content">
      <div class="about-header">
        <div class="about-avatar">🧠</div>
        <div>
          <div class="about-name">Chaeyeon Kim</div>
          <div class="about-subtitle">
            Minerva University · BA Social Science + Neuroscience<br>
            San Francisco, CA · Expected 2026
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="readme-content"><span class="comment">// who I am</span>
<span class="key">disciplines</span>  <span class="value">neuroscience · composition · film · software</span>
<span class="key">currently</span>    <span class="value">GenAI product strategy @ NTT Tokyo</span>
<span class="key">capstone</span>     <span class="value">The Body Conducts — EEG → music → film</span>
<span class="key">past</span>         <span class="value">Paramount · Harvard CoCoDev · UTDT Neurolab</span>

<span class="comment">// what I make</span>
I don't work across disciplines. I work at their intersection,
all at once — because the problems I care about live there.

Chronic stress is invisible. Science communication failed it.
So I wired electrodes to my skull, extracted my brainwaves,
and built a tool that converts raw neural data into music.

<span class="comment">// what I want</span>
To make Google's magic more magical.
The same way I made invisible biology audible.</div>
      <div class="tag-row">
        <span class="tag red">EEG → MIDI</span>
        <span class="tag blue">Logic Pro</span>
        <span class="tag">Python · R</span>
        <span class="tag blue">Film</span>
        <span class="tag">Psychoneuroimmunology</span>
        <span class="tag red">Science Art</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- WINDOW: CAPSTONE -->
  <div class="window" id="win-capstone">
    <div class="titlebar" onmousedown="startDrag(event, 'win-capstone')">
      <div class="traffic-lights">
        <div class="tl close" onclick="closeWindow('win-capstone')"></div>
        <div class="tl min"></div>
        <div class="tl max"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="titlebar-title">📁 The Body Conducts</div>
    </div>
    <div class="window-content">
      <div class="capstone-title">The Body Conducts</div>
      <div class="capstone-subtitle">EEG · Music · Film · Literature Review</div>

      <div class="mechanism-box">
<span class="highlight">stress trigger</span> → HPA axis → cortisol surge → cytokine upregulation
→ immune dysregulation → <span class="highlight">systemic inflammation</span>
→ body attacks itself
→ nobody can see it happening

<span style="color:#888;">// existing formats fail to make this felt</span>
<span style="color:#888;">// so I made it audible</span></div>

      <div class="section-label">What I Built</div>
      <p style="font-size:11px; line-height:1.7; color:#333;">
        Five original scores where <strong>my own EEG brainwaves</strong> — recorded under induced stress — are converted into a real-time spectral EQ filter that shapes what you hear. The audience isn't listening to music <em>about</em> stress. They're inside a physiological record of it.
      </p>

      <div class="section-label">The Films</div>
      <p style="font-size:11px; line-height:1.7; color:#333;">
        Three films. A female conductor whose orchestra refuses to sync — mirroring how chronic stress causes body systems to miscoordinate. Each character is an instrument. The Wolf is stress itself: jazz, unpredictable, impossible to resolve cleanly.
      </p>

      <div class="section-label">Why It Had To Exist</div>
      <p style="font-size:11px; line-height:1.7; color:#333;">
        No one had made chronic social stress <em>felt</em> through biometric data, music, and film simultaneously. It required being a neuroscientist, composer, filmmaker, and software engineer at once. I am all of them all at once.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- WINDOW: STRESS SIMULATOR -->
  <div class="window" id="win-stress">
    <div class="titlebar" onmousedown="startDrag(event, 'win-stress')">
      <div class="traffic-lights">
        <div class="tl close" onclick="closeWindow('win-stress')"></div>
        <div class="tl min"></div>
        <div class="tl max"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="titlebar-title">🧠 EEG Stress Simulator — Alpha Suppression Model</div>
    </div>
    <div class="window-content" style="padding:0; overflow:hidden;">
      <div id="stress-container">
        <canvas id="eeg-canvas"></canvas>
        <div id="stress-ui">
          <div id="stress-label">BASELINE</div>
          <div id="stress-bar-container">
            <div id="stress-bar"></div>
          </div>
          <div id="stress-desc">
            Alpha suppression: 0% · System at rest<br>
            <span id="eeg-reading" style="color:#4a90d9;">α power: high · HPA axis: inactive</span>
          </div>
          <button id="stress-btn" onclick="runStressSimulation()">▶ Induce Stress Condition</button>
          <div id="stress-mode-label">Simulating Chaeyeon's EEG pipeline · CapBaseline state</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- WINDOW: NOTEBOOKLM -->
  <div class="window" id="win-notebook">
    <div class="titlebar" onmousedown="startDrag(event, 'win-notebook')">
      <div class="traffic-lights">
        <div class="tl close" onclick="closeWindow('win-notebook')"></div>
        <div class="tl min"></div>
        <div class="tl max"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="titlebar-title">🎙️ NotebookLM — AI reads my brain</div>
    </div>
    <div class="window-content">
      <div class="notebook-intro">
        I uploaded my entire capstone into NotebookLM and let it generate a podcast about my own work. Then I watched it get some things right — and some things interestingly wrong. Below is what I pushed back on.
